Address/resolve point #21 in Editorial Notes for 04 NV:
AS: Ordering of foods / grouping (Banakou…)
I did not check for ordering of each row / entry in the Food names. For the most part, these seemed to follow a consistent approach (alphabetical order, with some exceptions relating to food prep, for example “raw” before “boiled”, etc.). However, I noticed (in passing), at least one place that seemed inconsistent (under Starchy roots, tubers and their products):
- Banakou né barâand kanss saagbo (Burkina Faso)*: Foutou of cassava and unripe plantain 
- Banakou né kou saagbo (Burkina Faso)*: Foutou of yam and cassava
- Banakou né barâand moomd saagbo (Burkina Faso)*: Foutou of cassava and ripe plantain 
RC: Agree. Change order.
VPdQ: We think it can just be done by sorting the items by alphabetical order again, right?
AJV: The short answer is no, sorry! The order of foods in Excel is: 1, By food group; 2, By food name, BUT raw foods come before their cooked counterparts (e.g. Plantain, unripe, pale flesh, raw comes before Plantain, unripe, pale flesh, boiled).
